<br>
It's just not worth it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=glasya>Glasya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#333333>(5/15/01 5:41:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: flamearc/shaman/druid</span><hr size=1> The beauty of Scintillation as opposed to any other PBAOE mages get is the radius, cast time and # of affected MOBs.  All other PBAOE are limited to 4, Scintillation is not limited (this is a huge dmg/mana ratio for more than 4 MOBs).  The cast time and recast delay are way better than any of out PBAOE spells.  And the effect area is all around you (at a sizable radius), so you can just stand in the middle and chain scintillate.  No other PBAOE is worthwhile in these groups for us.<br>
<br>
The shaman in the PBAOE group did not work for us.  The heals are too slow (compared to remedy), and the slow is not useful if the enchanter is chain casting.  It is also very hard to target MOBs for slow when AOE spells go off, they create a sizable lag on the client side video cards.  I have a GeForceII and the framerate drops sharply when it starts, enough that I can't see the mouse in the pixel mess not can I move it (had to make a hotkey for scintillation).<br>
<br>
Druids are tough for a similar reason, but since they do have an AOE that may work and they can use AOE snare/root to make sure no one gets away.<br>
<br>
<br>
I am curious if PBAOE groups can work at lower levels (before we get Scintillation)?<br>
